quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,94,"Whenever We sent a prophet to a town, We afflicted its people with suffering and adversity, so that they might humble themselves [before God]"
  7,95,"and then We changed their hardship into ease until they grew affluent and said, \"Our fathers had also experienced adversity and prosperity,\" then We seized them suddenly, unawares"
  7,96,"Had the people of those towns believed in and feared God, We would have showered upon them blessings from heaven and earth, but they rejected the truth. So We seized them on account of their misdeeds"
  7,97,Do the people of these towns now feel secure against the coming of Our punishment upon them by night while they are asleep
  7,98,"Or, do they feel secure against the coming of Our punishment upon them in the forenoon while they are at play"
  7,99,Do they feel secure against God's devising? No one feels secure against God's devising except for those doomed to ruin